📍Beaver Street Fisheries

Headquartered in Jacksonville for over 70 years, Beaver Street Fisheries (BSF) is an industry leader in importing, exporting, manufacturing and distributing quality frozen seafood and meats worldwide. 

The company is a family owned business now being run by the 4th generation. They are truly the definition of the American dream in action and we are so proud to have them right here in the 4th Congressional District! 

Employing around 500 people, BSF directly imports over 100 million pounds of product annually and exports/sells over 130 million pounds of products to customers from distribution points nationwide. 

We had a great tour and talk about the impact of tariffs, the ability to invest in more American product, and the successes/challenges they are seeing in their industry. 

Thank you for the great education about the seafood supply chain and its impact on the economy, @BSF_Corp! #BeanOnTour

📍Roller Die + Forming in Green Cove Springs

For nearly 9 decades, Roller Die + Forming has been a leading producer of standard and custom roll formed parts all over the world. In roll forming, sheet metal passes through a specific set of matched rolls. Each set of rolls touches the passing metal and changes the shape resulting in the desired cross section.

The Green Cove Springs facility produces many different parts for various industries including heavy truck, bus, medical, and building products. 

With locations across the United States, Roller Die made the decision to relocate their headquarters to Florida as our state has the most business friendly climate bar none. 

During the tour, we discussed the jobs their facility brought to the region, the successes they are seeing via tariffs, and how the One, Big Beautiful Bill boosts American manufacturing. 

Included in the One, Big Beautiful Bill: 

✅ Full expensing for new factories and factory improvements to accelerate domestic manufacturing.
✅ Full expensing for domestic R&D to encourage domestic innovation.
✅ Full expensing for new capital investments, like machinery and equipment, to boost domestic production.

I enjoyed spending time with the @Rollerdie team and learning more about their operations! #BeanOnTour #MadeInAmerica #Manufacturing

Earlier this week at @ManifestSpirits in downtown Jacksonville alongside the @USChamber and @JAXChamber, we hosted a roundtable discussion with local business leaders to discuss the pro-growth business tax provisions in the One, Big Beautiful Bill. 

Small businesses are the backbone of our local economy, and the One, Big Beautiful Bill is a pro-growth game-changer that gives local businesses the certainty they need to invest, expand, and hire. 

The One, Big Beautiful Bill: 

✅ Delivers permanent relief for small businesses
✅ No tax on tips, social security, and overtime
✅ Makes permanent 100 percent immediate expensing

We all know that when small businesses thrive, our communities thrive, and this legislation is helping make that happen.

Thank you to everyone who attended and took part in this important discussion! #BeanOnTour

We as a nation continue to mourn their loss and pray for their loved ones. We will never forget and always honor their courage, sacrifice, and service to our country.

Jacksonville is quickly becoming a dynamic financial hub. From its growing fintech footprint to its deep ties to logistics and trade, Jacksonville is a place where wise investment meets real-world momentum.

I had the opportunity to visit with @Fidelity to discuss tax policy, retirement reform, and the One, Big Beautiful Bill. 

This landmark legislation is more than a tax package—it’s a strategic reset for American growth and will serve as a catalyst for economic growth and investment opportunity. 

What does the One, Big Beautiful Bill do? 

✅ Makes permanent the reduced individual income tax rates from the 2017 Tax Cuts and Jobs Act—locking in brackets from 10% to 37%

✅ Additional $6,000 deduction for seniors over 65 enhances retirement income planning

✅ Reintroduces 100% bonus depreciation to encourage capital investment 

This bill strengthens key industries, supports job creation, and fuels innovation. 

Thanks for the time and discussion, Fidelity! #BeanOnTour

🚒 Clay County Fire Station 20 is now in service!

This station is located at 1305 Idlewild Avenue in Green Cove Springs.

Station 20 is a state-of-the-art facility designed to meet the needs of our growing community—with advanced safety features and increased space for more firefighters, equipment, and vehicles.

This station also has Clay County's first 9/11 Memorial. In front of the station, you will see the display of two beams of exterior wall structural steel, reported to have been from the 68th floor of World Trade Center 1, the North Tower. Additionally, a sapling from a Callery pear tree that once stood at the original World Trade Center, now known as the Survivor Tree, will also be planted at the Memorial.

The #BeanTeam was honored to join @ClayFireRescue, @ClayCo_FL, and the community for the Official Opening Ceremony of Station 20! 

Thank you to everyone who made this station possible!

The brand-new Jean Ribault High School is a 21st century modern learning space designed to accommodate up to 1,700 students. This state-of-the-art campus includes:

🎉 Congratulations @RibaultTrojans on your new campus! Wishing you all a successful school year.

🛣️ Clay County’s newest major county road, Cathedral Oak Parkway, is officially OPEN!! 

Yesterday, District Staff attended the Official Ribbon Cutting for Cathedral Oak Parkway which is a newly constructed, five-mile county road spanning from Shadowlawn Elementary School to the First Coast Expressway and continuing towards U.S. 17 in Green Cove Springs.

Our team was honored to work with @ClayCo_FL and the Army Corps of Engineers to obtain the necessary approvals to get this project moving forward. 

The project was designed to improve daily commutes, ease congestion, and provide a more direct route through the heart of the county.

Congratulations on the successful completion of this project and thank you to WGI, Clay County, and all involved for making this a reality!

💡Did you know yesterday, August 7th, was National Lighthouse Day?

To celebrate, I attended the Amelia Island Lighthouse Grand Re-Opening. Built in 1838, this is the oldest lighthouse in the state and has stood watch over Florida’s coastline as a beacon of hope guiding vessels home for nearly two centuries. 

Last year, I got a call from my son who was serving as the Mayor and he informed me the lighthouse needed a new beacon. Our team immediately went to work joining colleagues from Northeast Florida and the U.S. Coast Guard Auxiliary in the effort to refurbish her brilliant beacon. 

Thanks to the dedication of city leaders and the collaboration of our local, state, and federal partners, this historic renovation has come to fruition—restoring her beauty and safeguarding her legacy for generations to come.

This lighthouse isn’t just a landmark to me; it’s a part of my childhood, a symbol of the community that raised me, and a reminder of how lucky I am to call this place home.

To everyone who contributed to this restoration, THANK YOU!!

The One Big Beautiful Bill is a game-changer for ICE & Border Patrol—giving our frontline heroes the tools, resources, and accountability they need to do the job safely and effectively.

Raids don’t run on rhetoric—they run on real support.

One year ago today, the attempted assassination of President Trump in Butler, PA, stunned the nation and the world.
